
// This Hyperlambda code snippet updates the value of the [.sql] node by concatenating its current value with the string " default " and the value of the [pkDefault] node from the [.arguments] node set. It uses [set-value] to modify the [.sql] node, [strings.concat] to concatenate the strings, and [get-value] to retrieve the current [.sql] value and the [pkDefault] value.
set-value:x:@.sql
   strings.concat
      get-value:x:@.sql
      .:" default "
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/pkDefault
